3. In Archive existing file, change File to Move to:
   body('Check_existing_live_file')?['value'][1]?['{Identifier}']
This grabs the second item in the array (index 1) instead of the first. If SharePoint consistently returns [folder, file] order, the file is always at index 1. Worth trying as a quick test before going deeper into syntax debugging.

Or actually the cleanest workaround: use a name filter instead of an IsFolder filter. The file is always called CAP_to_BU_Mapping.xlsx — filter on that:
In Filter files only advanced mode:
@equals(item()?['Name'], 'CAP_to_BU_Mapping.xlsx')
This avoids the IsFolder property entirely and just matches by exact filename.
